definition: to come in
to go forward/to advance/to go in/to enter/to put in/to submit/to take in/to admit/(math.) base of a number system/classifier for sections in a building or residential compound
to come/to arrive/to come round/ever since/next

sentences.english: He came in, holding a cigarette between his lips.
sentences.chinese: 他嘴上叨着香烟走了进来。

sentences.english: At this moment the cannon of the harbor is heard firing, and Suzuki hurries in, saying that it is a warship.
sentences.chinese: 就在这时港口一声炮响，铃木跑进来说是一艘军舰。

sentences.english: The fruit crop was now in.
In answer to the ring, appeared a page boy with a silver soup tureen.
sentences.chinese: 按过铃，一个小男仆就捧了一只盛汤的银器进来。

sentences.english: At last his rapier flew into the corner of the room.
sentences.chinese: 最后他的剑飞进来了房屋的角落。

sentences.english: When I take a shower, he grabs a magazine and sits on the toilet, reading.
sentences.chinese: 我洗澡时他拿了本杂志进来坐在马桶上念。
他骂骂咧咧地走了进来。
不要把星巴克咖啡带进来。

sentences.english: This is where Greece may come in.
sentences.chinese: 这也是希腊加入进来的原因。

sentences.english: Come in by the back door, then no one will notice you.
sentences.chinese: 从后门进来，那样没有人注意你。

sentences.english: Four people enter looking around in a curios way.
sentences.chinese: 有四个人走了进来，好奇的四处张望。

sentences.english: When I am about to nod off in the office, the boss walked in.
sentences.chinese: 我在办公室刚刚欲睡，老板走了进来。

sentences.english: At the Vanity Fair party, they were let in the back door.
sentences.chinese: 在《名利场》杂志的聚会上，他们从后门进来。

sentences.english: Lily runs into her in the stairwell one day.
sentences.chinese: 一天，李莉在楼梯间偶然碰到新拌进来的女孩。

sentences.english: Mr Earnshaw has a mind to shoot you, if you persist in endeavouring to enter.''
sentences.chinese: ‘如果你坚持要进来，恩萧先生打算拿枪崩你。’

sentences.english: Crowds poured in all the morning.
sentences.chinese: 整个上午，人们不断涌进来。
